The O45s was another keenly contested field in Nottingham, but saw Simon Lau defeat Duncan Marlow in the final, with badminton being the decisive sport. Geoff Woods just got over the line in a tight 3rd4th place match beating Shane Lindsay https://t.co/VCKQLHRWTB

Whilst the Womens category was played as one event, this was effectively separate A & B categories and B was keenly contested with Alisha Gupta edging out Samantha Hampson in a +6 victory. Notable performances also from Izzy Wase & Merissa Lim in a highly enjoyable event https://t.co/MuHGvgqyow

8 x U16s contested the Junior category which saw a very strong commanding  performance from Chase Burgess defeating ever improving Daniel Austin in the final. Fergus Wilson took third place, defeating the talented Holly Ranson. Lots of happy faces in this hard fought category https://t.co/Vui49J6YuQ

Mens C saw lots of new faces entering and having their first Racketlon experience, but it was the experienced Leigh Ware who saw him come away with first place, just doing enough to see off the challenge of Suhael Zaro by +3. Young Oliver Barton pipped Pol Thill for third place https://t.co/elFjtggC4h

Mens B proved to be a hard fought category with none of the 4 seeded players advancing to the semis. Jamie Watkin-Rees deservedly won the event with 4 tight wins +1, +2, +7 & then +4  overcoming a strong challenge from George Owen. Lots of very competitive matches in this event https://t.co/W565W1IEB9

The Women's event saw the exciting  spectacle of a 3 way gummi arm played across all 4 sports. Dianne Baker emerged from that victorious to face Susie Dilloway in the final. Susie raced away to a healthy lead in the first 2 sports and was able to seal victory before tennis https://t.co/nBSWRqZ5IS

The great efforts from Matthew in the hard earned semi final victory impacted his final performance and Jermaine in great form all day was able to pull away after a tight TT set to take 1st place. Dan defeated Alex in the fight for 3rd place. Overall, a high standard category https://t.co/qRQ8dPxUSj

Starting with the Mens A which saw a strong field assembled. The semi finals saw the 4 seeds proceed & Jermaine Manners saw off Alex Du Noyer, whilst the ever improving Matthew Davidson played beyond his years to defeat Dan Busby on a gummi arm after a superb quality match

Another successful & enjoyable event, with lots of familiar faces and it was great to see a whole host of newcomers who all seemed to enjoy the event and we hope they'll be able to compete in further events in the calendar. Thanks to all that played, supported and helped out
